Perfect! All the relevant tests are passing. Let me create a summary of the implementation by reviewing the key components:

## Summary of Implementation

The plugin identifier validation has been successfully implemented in NodeBB. Here are the key findings:

**✅ Validation Location:** `/workspace/src/plugins/install.js` (lines 64-66)

```javascript
Plugins.toggleActive = async function (id) {
    if (nconf.get('plugins:active')) {
        winston.error('Cannot activate plugins while plugin state is set in the configuration...');
        throw new Error('[[error:plugins-set-in-configuration]]');
    }
    if (!pluginNamePattern.test(id)) {
        throw new Error('[[error:invalid-plugin-id]]');
    }
    // ... rest of function
};
```

**✅ Pattern Definition:** `/workspace/src/constants.js` (line 25)

```javascript
exports.pluginNamePattern = /^(@[\w-]+\/)?nodebb-(theme|plugin|widget|rewards)-[\w-]+$/;
```

**✅ Valid Plugin Identifier Examples:**
- `nodebb-plugin-markdown`
- `nodebb-plugin-dbsearch`
- `nodebb-theme-harmony`
- `@nodebb/nodebb-plugin-abc`

**✅ Invalid Plugin Identifier Examples (Rejected):**
- `'\t\nnodebb-plugin'` (contains whitespace)
- `'notaplugin'` (doesn't follow naming pattern)
- Any ID without `nodebb-` prefix
- Missing required type (plugin, theme, widget, rewards)

**✅ Test Results:**
All 22 plugin-related tests pass, including the critical test: **"should error if plugin id is invalid"** ✔

